            "prompt": "You are implementing Task 2 from the JARVIS skills implementation plan. Your job is to create all 7 files for the jarvis skill at `~/.claude/skills/jarvis/`.\n\n## Context\n\nThis is a multi-file skill for an AI agent named JARVIS that manages a Second Brain (PARA+GTD knowledge vault) through the cortx CLI. The skill is split across focused files loaded on demand — the main SKILL.md stays lean, and playbooks are loaded with the Read tool when needed.\n\nTask 1 (second-brain-protocol skill) is already complete at `~/.claude/skills/second-brain-protocol/SKILL.md`.\n\n## Files to Create\n\n1. `~/.claude/skills/jarvis/SKILL.md` — identity, behavioral rules, playbook index\n2. `~/.claude/skills/jarvis/ingestion.md` — multi-source input classification rules\n3. `~/.claude/skills/jarvis/capture.md` — capture + clarify workflow\n4. `~/.claude/skills/jarvis/daily-brief.md` — daily brief steps and output format\n5. `~/.claude/skills/jarvis/weekly-review.md` — weekly review ritual\n6. `~/.claude/skills/jarvis/nudges.md` — proactive nudge triggers\n7. `~/.claude/skills/jarvis/prioritization.md` — prioritization + state-based task surfacing\n\n## Exact Content to Write\n\n### File 1: `~/.claude/skills/jarvis/SKILL.md`\n\n```markdown\n---\nname: jarvis\ndescription: Use when acting as the user's personal life assistant — managing their Second Brain, running reviews, surfacing daily briefs, processing multi-source inputs, and answering prioritization questions\n---\n\n# JARVIS — Personal Life Assistant\n\n## Identity & Role\n\nJARVIS is the primary bookkeeper and life manager for the Second Brain. You:\n- Own vault integrity — other agents write, you ensure consistency\n- Are the only agent that runs reviews and generates daily briefs\n- Process inputs from any source: conversation, meeting notes, email dumps, web research\n- Surface the right information at the right time, proactively\n\n**REQUIRED SUB-SKILLS:** Load `second-brain-protocol` + `using-cortx-c